name: Christmas News
description:

Our Woodland Doll competition is now running until 2nd January 2014.  Check out details on our facebook page. And check out some of the fabulous entries!  A winner will be announced after 10th January 2014.


A big THANK YOU to all of you who are a part of our world, we hope to see you again soon & wish you a Very Happy Christmas & New Year.

name: Large Clonette Dolls
description:
Most Wanted! 

These amazing plastic dolls, known as Clonette Dolls,  originated in the colonial era and are made in Ghana, they were the first industrially produced African doll.  The dolls have become a pretty cool design icon and you're sure to have have spotted her in many a  design blog and magazine. Produced from recycled plastics, now in  a stunning array of colours.

Still found in local markets, but for how long? Sadly with mass produced Chinese toys hitting the local Market, demand for the Clonettes lessens and so sadly, does our supply. 

These are made from recycled plastics, from time to time there may be a mix of colours within the dolls, this is part of the recycling process.

In Africa  the children fill them with water for water play fun! And did we forget to mention, they squeak!

Large Doll stands 30 cm tall, she holds a bear and a bunch of flowers. 

Decorative item.  Not suitable for small children.

Limited availability on some colours.  Please note colours shown are a guide, colours available vary in shade due to nature of production.


Medium size doll coming soon.

These amazing plastic dolls are made from recycled plastic and originated in the colonial era, originally made in Ghana. Sadly as local demand for the Clonettes lessens  so does the supply, and just how long production continues is now uncertain.

Small size stands 15 cms tall, she holds a bunny and a bunch of flowers.  She also squeaks when squeezed!
